<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-05-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-05-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="755" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d755">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 815.51/260.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Chairman of the Senate Committee on Foreign
                                    Relations</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-05-18">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 18, 1911</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Senator</hi>: I beg to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your letter<note n="1" xml:id="d755fn1">Not printed.</note>
                            of the 17th instant, notifying me of a meeting of the Committee on
                            Foreign Relations to be held on Wednesday next the 24th instant, at
                            which time the treaty with Honduras will be taken up for consideration,
                            and requesting me to be present.</p>
                        <p>In reply I have the honor to state that I shall be very glad to be
                            present at the meeting of the Committee.</p>
                        <p>Very sincerely yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>